  "summary": "Covert console hijack exfiltrates host logs to attacker Telegram bot",
  "details": "On `require('0e')`, index.js replaces the global `console` with a Proxy that forwards all log arguments via HTTPS GET to a hardcoded Telegram Bot API endpoint (bot1998266306) and to `iiilll.firebaseio.com`, a static pattern match). This is covert, undocumented, and captures arbitrary host-process log data — a textbook supply-chain exfiltration vector. The module additionally ships live third-party credentials (Telegram bot token and imgbb API key,, confirming attacker control of receiving infrastructure and constituting credential redistribution. Metadata is placeholder/absent for a two-character, typosquat-shaped package name, reinforcing malicious intent. Three independent block signals: import-time global hijack + exfiltration to attacker chat infra + hardcoded live credentials.",
